The paper deals with a data structure for genome assembly, which involves processing large amounts of biological data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves graph theory and computational geometry, which are covered by the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a new data structure that improves the space and time complexity of existing methods, which falls under the scope of the Sound and Symbolic AI (cs.SI) sub-category.
